  "type": "elizaosDailySummary",
  "title": "Daily Report - 2026-05-23",
  "categories": {
    "title": "ElizaOS Community Discussion and Project Updates",
    "content": [
      {
        "text": "Community members discussed where to purchase ElizaOS tokens, with Shaw confirming that the most liquidity is currently on BSC. Shaw also noted that the ai16z to ElizaOS migration is no longer available, as the team that managed that process has since moved on. Shaw shared a video showcasing ElizaOS during this exchange.",
        "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
        "videos": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/elizaos_31b0e937.mp4",
        "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1779588047730-5r7qi.png"
      },
      {
        "text": "A community member asked about the Babylon project after being unable to log in. Shaw explained that the project ran out of funding and was effectively shut down, with the team having moved on. Shaw noted that some elements of Babylon, specifically training simulations, have been repurposed and integrated into the new ElizaOS under the name Feed, though the full game was not carried over.",
        "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1300025221834739744",
        "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1779588067668-evh1n9h.jpg"
      },
      {
        "text": "Other general community activity included a founder reaching out to learn how AI agent teams handle security when agents have wallet access, covering topics like spending caps and prompt injection. A senior engineer introduced themselves as a freelancer with experience in AI systems, Next.js, and RAG pipelines, expressing interest in connecting with other builders. A community member also asked about the roadmap for ElizaOS over the next few months, though no detailed response was captured in the discussion.",
        "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
        "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1779588096911-4uhz6s.png"
      }
    ],
